The resonance condition for an electron spin is  

\[
h\nu = g\mu_{\mathrm B}B .
\]

Hence the magnetic field for the centre of the spectrum is  

\[
B_{0}= \frac{h\nu}{g\mu_{\mathrm B}}
      =\frac{9.5\times10^{9}\,\text{Hz}}
             {2.005\;\frac{\mu_{\mathrm B}}{h}}
      =\frac{9.5\times10^{9}}
             {2.005\;(1.3996\times10^{10}\,\text{Hz·T}^{-1})}
      \approx 0.3386\;\text{T}=338.6\;\text{mT}.
\]

The hyper‑fine splitting of the two lines is \(\Delta\nu = 280\;\text{MHz}=2.80\times10^{8}\,\text{Hz}\).  
In field units  

\[
\Delta B = \frac{\Delta\nu}{g\mu_{\mathrm B}/h}
         = \frac{2.80\times10^{8}}
                {2.005\;(1.3996\times10^{10})}
         \approx 9.99\;\text{mT}.
\]

The two lines are therefore at  

\[
B_{\pm}=B_{0}\pm\frac{\Delta B}{2}.
\]

The higher‑field line is  

\[
B_{\text{high}} = 338.6\;\text{mT} + \frac{9.99\;\text{mT}}{2}
                \approx 343.6\;\text{mT}.
\]

