The activation free‑energy difference is obtained from the Eyring relation  

\[
k=\frac{k_{\mathrm B}T}{h}\,e^{-\Delta G^{\ddagger}/RT}
\qquad\Longrightarrow\qquad
\Delta G^{\ddagger}= -RT\ln\!\left(\frac{k\,h}{k_{\mathrm B}T}\right)
\]

Hence the difference between the uncatalyzed and catalyzed reactions is  

\[
\Delta\Delta G^{\ddagger}
= \Delta G^{\ddagger}_{\text{uncat}}-\Delta G^{\ddagger}_{\text{cat}}
= -RT\ln\!\left(\frac{k_{\text{uncat}}}{k_{\text{cat}}\!}\right)
\]

\[
\frac{k_{\text{uncat}}}{k_{\text{cat}}}
= \frac{1.0\times10^{-15}\,\text{s}^{-1}}{14\,\text{s}^{-1}}
= 7.14\times10^{-17}
\]

\[
\ln\!\left(7.14\times10^{-17}\right)= -37.2
\]

\[
RT = (8.314\;\text{J mol}^{-1}\text{K}^{-1})(298.15\;\text{K}) = 2.48\times10^{3}\;\text{J mol}^{-1}
\]

\[
\Delta\Delta G^{\ddagger}= -RT\bigl[-37.2\bigr]
= (2.48\times10^{3}\;\text{J mol}^{-1})(37.2)
\approx 9.2\times10^{4}\;\text{J mol}^{-1}
= 9.2\times10^{1}\;\text{kJ mol}^{-1}
\]

\[
\boxed{92}\ \text{kJ/mol}
\]

