The coated hollow‑fiber membrane can be treated as two resistances in series (the polysulfone skin and the silicone‑rubber coating).  
For a gas \(i\)

\[
\frac{1}{(P/\ell)_{\text{eff},i}}=\frac{\ell_{\text{PSF}}}{P_{\text{PSF},i}}+
\frac{\ell_{\text{SiR}}}{P_{\text{SiR},i}}
\]

where  

* \(\ell_{\text{PSF}} = 1000\;\text{Å}=1.0\times10^{-5}\,\text{cm}\) (effective skin thickness)  
* \(\ell_{\text{SiR}} = 1\;\mu\text{m}=1.0\times10^{-4}\,\text{cm}\) (silicone‑rubber coating)  

Typical gas‑permeability data (at 35 °C, 1 atm) are  

\[
\begin{aligned}
P_{\text{PSF,CO}_2}&\approx 0.20\;\text{Barrer}, &
P_{\text{SiR,CO}_2}&\approx 300\;\text{Barrer},\\[2mm]
P_{\text{PSF,CH}_4}&\approx 0.05\;\text{Barrer}, &
P_{\text{SiR,CH}_4}&\approx 100\;\text{Barrer}.
\end{aligned}
\]

---

### 1.  Effective permeance for CO\(_2\)

\[
\begin{aligned}
\frac{1}{(P/\ell)_{\text{eff,CO}_2}}
&=\frac{1.0\times10^{-5}}{0.20}
  +\frac{1.0\times10^{-4}}{300}  \\
&=5.0\times10^{-5}+3.33\times10^{-7}
  \approx5.03\times10^{-5}\;\text{cm\,Barrer}^{-1}.
\end{aligned}
\]

\[
(P/\ell)_{\text{eff,CO}_2}
=\frac{1}{5.03\times10^{-5}}
\approx1.99\times10^{4}\;\frac{\text{Barrer}}{\text{cm}}.
\]

To express the permeance in the usual unit GPU (1 GPU = 10⁻⁶ cm³ (STP)/(cm²·s·cm Hg)):

\[
(P/\ell)_{\text{eff,CO}_2}
=1.99\times10^{4}\;\frac{\text{Barrer}}{\text{cm}}\times10^{4}
\approx2.0\times10^{8}\;\text{GPU}.
\]

\[
\boxed{2.0\times10^{8}\ \text{GPU}}
\]

---

### 2.  Permselectivity CO\(_2\)/CH\(_4\)

First obtain the effective permeance for CH\(_4\):

\[
\begin{aligned}
\frac{1}{(P/\ell)_{\text{eff,CH}_4}}
&=\frac{1.0\times10^{-5}}{0.05}
  +\frac{1.0\times10^{-4}}{100}  \\
&=2.0\times10^{-4}+1.0\times10^{-6}
  \approx2.01\times10^{-4}\;\text{cm\,Barrer}^{-1},
\end{aligned}
\]

\[
(P/\ell)_{\text{eff,CH}_4}
=\frac{1}{2.01\times10^{-4}}
\approx4.98\times10^{3}\;\frac{\text{Barrer}}{\text{cm}}.
\]

The permselectivity is the ratio of the two permeances:

\[
\alpha_{\text{CO}_2/\text{CH}_4}
=\frac{(P/\ell)_{\text{eff,CO}_2}}
       {(P/\ell)_{\text{eff,CH}_4}}
\approx\frac{1.99\times10^{4}}{4.98\times10^{3}}
\approx4.0.
\]

\[
\boxed{4}
\]

---

**Result**

- Effective permeance of the coated membrane for CO\(_2\): \(\displaystyle 2.0\times10^{8}\ \text{GPU}\)  
- Permselectivity CO\(_2\)/CH\(_4\): \(\displaystyle 4\).

