The enthalpy change for the isothermal expansion (which, for sublimation of a solid of negligible volume, equals the molar enthalpy of sublimation) is obtained from the \(pV\)‑term:

\[
\Delta H_{\text{sub}} \;=\; \Delta (pV)
\;=\; P_{\text{ext}}\;\Delta V
\;=\; P_{\text{ext}}\;\frac{V_f-V_i}{n}
\]

\[
\begin{aligned}
\Delta V &= 30.0\;\text{dm}^3-10.0\;\text{dm}^3 = 20.0\;\text{dm}^3
          = 20.0\times10^{-3}\;\text{m}^3 = 2.0\times10^{-2}\;\text{m}^3,\\[4pt]
P_{\text{ext}} &= 1.00\;\text{bar}=1.00\times10^{5}\;\text{Pa},\\[4pt]
n &= 3.00\;\text{mol}.
\end{aligned}
\]

\[
\Delta H_{\text{sub}}
= \frac{(1.00\times10^{5}\;\text{Pa})(2.0\times10^{-2}\;\text{m}^3)}{3.00}
= \frac{2.0\times10^{3}\;\text{J}}{3.00}
= 6.67\times10^{2}\;\text{J mol}^{-1}
= 0.667\;\text{kJ mol}^{-1}.
\]

\[
\boxed{0.667}\ \text{kJ mol}^{-1}
\]

The overall charging reaction is the reverse of the discharge reaction  

\[
\mathrm{LiCoO_2}+6\mathrm{C}\;\longrightarrow\;\mathrm{CoO_2}+ \mathrm{LiC_6}
\]

Thus lithium is transferred from the cathode material \(\mathrm{LiCoO_2}\) to the graphite anode, forming \(\mathrm{LiC_6}\).

---

### 1.  Moles of the starting materials  

\[
\begin{aligned}
M_{\mathrm{LiCoO_2}} &= 6.941+58.933+2(15.999)=97.872\;\text{g mol}^{-1}\\[2pt]
n_{\mathrm{LiCoO_2}} &=\frac{10.00\;\text{g}}{97.872\;\text{g mol}^{-1}}
                     =0.102176\;\text{mol}
\end{aligned}
\]

\[
M_{\mathrm{C}} = 12.011\;\text{g mol}^{-1},\qquad
n_{\mathrm{C}} =\frac{10.00\;\text{g}}{12.011\;\text{g mol}^{-1}}
               =0.8326\;\text{mol}
\]

The stoichiometry requires \(6\) mol C per mol \(\mathrm{LiCoO_2}\); the needed amount of C is  

\[
6\,n_{\mathrm{LiCoO_2}} = 6(0.102176)=0.61306\;\text{mol}
\]

Since \(n_{\mathrm{C}} > 0.61306\) mol, \(\mathrm{LiCoO_2}\) is the limiting reagent.

---

### 2.  Lithium transferred  

Each mole of \(\mathrm{LiCoO_2}\) supplies one mole of Li:

\[
m_{\mathrm{Li}} = n_{\mathrm{LiCoO_2}}\;M_{\mathrm{Li}}
                =0.102176\;\text{mol}\times 6.941\;\text{g mol}^{-1}
                =0.7095\;\text{g}
\]

---

