The anode initially contains 10.00 g of graphite. After charging, the same graphite plus the transferred lithium constitute the anode:

\[
m_{\text{anode, charged}} = 10.00\;\text{g} + 0.7095\;\text{g}
                           = 10.7095\;\text{g}
\]

Rounded to the appropriate number of significant figures (four),  

\[
\boxed{10.71}\ \text{g}
\]

